12 July 2016The Deputy Minister of Communications, Ms Stella Ndabeni Abrahams will, on Wednesday 13 July 2016, interact with elderly citizens in Nyanga, Western Cape.The outreach programme will include serving the elderly citizens, pampering, blankets handover and activity-based competitions under the theme, a healthy life is a long and prosperous life. This programme is in commemoration of Nelson Mandela International Day which provides a clarion call to action for people to recognise their ability to have a positive effect on others around them. Mandela Day further inspires people to embrace the values that the late former president shared, and ultimately seeks to empower communities everywhere to Take Action; Inspire Change; and Make Every Day a Mandela Day. Members of the media are therefore invited to be part of this community outreach programme which will take place as follows:Date: 13 July 2016 Venue: KTC Hall, Nyanga, Western Cape Time: 9h00 15h00Journalists will be afforded interviews and photo opportunities.For media RSVP please contact Louis Botha Cell: 073 427 1917 E-mail: LouisB@gcis.gov.zaEnquiries: Nthabeleng Mokitimi-Dlamini Cell: 073 222 5522Issued by Department of Commonucations